{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/justtext\/jtrealmap"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTRealMap"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"text":"#define","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"JTRealMap","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"mapper"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"sep","kind":"internalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"extractor","kind":"internalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"arg"},{"kind":"text","text":", ...)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It is so real. It was first called ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecursiveMap"},{"type":"text","text":", but Real is cooler and shorter."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"So all this map does is exactly what you’d expect."}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It applies our ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"mapper"},{"type":"text","text":" macro to the first argument (out of the arguments we need to process)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If more arguments are left in the list, we put down our separator with the help of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"extractor"},{"type":"text","text":","}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"After the extracted separator, we need to somehow call ","type":"text"},{"code":"JTRealMap","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to process all other elements"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"C macros can’t directly call themselves, so we use a trick I picked up from this article:","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"https:\/\/www.scs.stanford.edu\/~dm\/blog\/va-opt.html"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Idea of the trick is that we can defer the invokation of this ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTRealMapRef","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(which would eventually give us our RealMap back) by putting "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTParens","type":"reference"},{"text":" macro instead","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of the real parentheses. So it will require an extra expansion to evaluate this thing, and that means,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when it is evaluated, all the bits and stuff for our initial "},{"code":"JTRealMap","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" macro will be cleared, it will be expanded again,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"finally creating our so desired recursion! So, because of these delayed operations, preprocessor forgets that it has","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"already expanded our "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"JTRealMap"},{"text":" macro. Still don’t understand it in comlete details, stuff about replacing bits, but the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"basic idea is this."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because we are just using this "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"__VA_OPT__"},{"type":"text","text":" thing, the implementation is really straightforwrad here."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"We don’t have to explicitly clear any bits (still not sure if it’s even possible), or try to implement this ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"__VA_OPT__"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from scratch, which is actually not as easy as it may seem."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Internal Separator Extractors","identifiers":["doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTParensSepExtractor","doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTSepProducerExtractor","doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTPlainSepExtractor","doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTCommonMap","doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTRealMapRef"],"anchor":"Internal-Separator-Extractors"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Actual ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"recursivish"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" macro to map the arguments","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"JTRealMap","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"JTRealMap","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"macro","title":"JTRealMap","externalID":"c:Sequences.h@659@macro@JTRealMap","roleHeading":"Macro","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"JustText"}]},"sections":[],"references":{"doc://JustText/documentation/JustText":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/justtext","title":"JustText","abstract":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"After all, it’s just a bunch of text"}],"type":"emphasis"}],"role":"collection","type":"topic"},"doc://JustText/documentation/JustText/JTPlainSepExtractor":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/justtext\/jtplainsepextractor","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Just return the separator as is"}],"title":"JTPlainSepExtractor","fragments":[{"text":"JTPlainSepExtractor","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/JustText\/documentation\/JustText\/JTPlainSepExtractor"},"doc://JustText/documentation/JustText/JTCommonMap":{"kind":"symbol","title":"JTCommonMap","url":"\/documentation\/justtext\/jtcommonmap","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"J